@page "/"

<PageTitle>CricketClub Home</PageTitle>

<div class="container my-4">
    <h1 class="display-4 mb-3">🏏 CricketClub</h1>

    <p class="lead">
        Welcome to <strong>CricketClub</strong> – a full-stack .NET 10 / C# 14
        playground for building a realistic cricket club management platform.
    </p>

    <hr class="my-4" />

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h4">What this site will eventually do</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Manage teams, seasons, and fixtures.</li>
            <li>Track live scoring, match results, and detailed stats.</li>
            <li>Provide a member portal for availability and selection.</li>
            <li>Offer admin tools for club officials and captains.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h4">Week 1 Goal</h2>
        <p>
            Right now, we are in <strong>Week 1</strong>, setting up the foundation:
            solution structure, Web API health checks, and this Blazor shell.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2 class="h4">Next Steps</h2>
        <p>
            In upcoming weeks, this site will connect to the CricketClub Web API,
            show real fixtures, and provide member features.
        </p>
    </section>
</div>
